Popular crossdresser James Brown has said the most miserable time of his life was when he lived with his mother for one year. Brown said this during an interview on ‘Tea with Tay’ live podcast. The controversial crossdresser said that he never really lived with his mom while growing up but he would never forget his one-year experience living with her.   Onyeka Onwenu opens up on abuse in marriage     Christiana Boluwade to premiere Alantakun     Zee One to celebrate 2022 Valentine with Bollywood love…   James said that he has not seen his mom for ten years now and when asked why he hasn’t spoken to his mother, he simply said “because we don’t talk.” “She wasn’t serious with children but now she changed, I don’t know what she’s doing now, it’s been ten years I saw her last.” - Advertisement - “I only stayed with my mom for a year, I was 6 or 7 years old. That was the most miserable time of my life because she messed with my mentality. I was the most quite person then,” James Brown said.